Title: Object: La Malincolia!
Description: St Thais seated on the ground with her right hand resting on her cheek, at left is a vase on a ledge; copy of an etching by Parmigianino. 16 February 1824 Etching on thin paper
Curator's comments: See M.41.28 for another impression. See W,2.89 for Parmigianino's etching.
Bibliographic references: Bartsch / Le Peintre graveur (XVI.12.10.II) (copy in the same direction)
Associated names: Representation of: St Thais of Egypt
